1 AN ACT concerning energy; relating to electric transmission development;
2 requiring legislative approval prior to the construction of high-impact
3 electric transmission lines; amending K.S.A. 66-1,177 and 66-1,178
4 and repealing the existing sections.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 66-1,177 is hereby amended to read as follows: 66-
8 1,177. As used in this act, the following terms shall have the meanings
9 ascribed to them herein:
10 (a) "Electric utility" means every public utility, as defined by K.S.A.
11 66-104, which and amendments thereto, that owns, controls, operates or
12 manages any equipment, plant or generating machinery for the production,
13 transmission, delivery or furnishing, of electricity or electric power;
14 (b) "Electric transmission lines line" means any line or extension of a
15 line which that is at least five (5) miles in length and which is used for the
16 bulk transfer of two hundred thirty (230) kilovolts or more of electricity;
17 (c) "Commission" means the state corporation commission.
18 (d) "High-impact electric transmission line" means any line or
19 extension of a line that is at least 10 miles in length and used for the bulk
20 transfer of 340 kilovolts or more of electricity.
21 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 66-1,178 is hereby amended to read as follows: 66-
22 1,178. (a) No electric utility may begin site preparation for or construction
23 of an electric transmission line, or exercise the right of eminent domain to
24 acquire any interest in land in connection with the site preparation for a
25 construction of any such line without:
26 (1) First acquiring a siting permit from the commission; and
27 (2) if such line is a high-impact electric transmission line, also
28 acquiring the approval of the legislature in accordance with subsection
29 (c).
30 (b) (1) Whenever any electric utility desires to obtain such a siting
31 permit, the utility shall file an application with the commission setting
32 forth therein that the utility proposes to construct an electric transmission
33 line and specifying:
34 (1) (A) The proposed location thereof;
35 (2)(B) the names and addresses of the landowners of record whose
36 land or interest therein is proposed to be acquired in connection with the

